  "text": "The purpose of the guidelines in general and, therefore, also of the EAU and AUA guidelines is not to be prescriptive as to how a clinician should treat a patient, but rather to provide a guide and an authoritative reference on the most appropriate clinical pathway currently available. Clinical practice guidelines are considered good tools for controlling and improving the effectiveness and efficiency of medical care [CITATION_1] . However, it is a common concern that the publication of guidelines does not necessarily influence clinical practice. Passive dissemination is generally ineffective in changing physicians' behavior [CITATION_2] .",
